## Context
The §2.3 machinery of measurement — Rio markers, UNFCCC reporting, the rival
donor and recipient regimes, and the OECD expert groups that set the terms — is
described too abstractly. Reviewer 2 wants the who/where/how made concrete, and
the Desrosieres quote connected to the empirical case. Complements the Mitchell
aid-apparatus cite already landed (PR #901). Tracker: 0141.

## Relevant passages
- `content/manuscript.qmd` §2.3 — Rio markers role/functioning; UNFCCC reporting;
  donor-vs-recipient competing regimes; OECD expert groups "set terms of debate";
  accountability-vocabulary crystallisation; the Desrosieres quote (p7).

## Actions
1. Rio markers: reporting context, by whom, for what purpose.
2. UNFCCC reporting: to whom, by whom, for what purpose.
3. Contrast the donor-side and recipient-side measurement regimes (MDB vs DAC)
   as competing, not complementary.
4. OECD expert groups "set the terms of debate": when, where, who, methods, which
   debates — with examples of accountability vocabulary crystallising.
5. Connect the Desrosieres quote (p7) to the empirical case rather than leaving it
   free-standing; add sources to §2.3.

## Test (prose ratchet)
- Negative guard only; keep the Desrosieres/Porter and Mitchell 2002 cites intact.

## Exit criteria
- [ ] §2.3 measurement-regime passages revised with concrete actors/methods/dates
- [ ] Desrosieres quote tied to the empirical case
- [ ] Cover-letter traceability rows updated with §ref + commit SHA
- [ ] Prose in the author's voice per `docs/style-anchor-v205.md`; `make check-fast` green
